INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'b2807e18-d9ea-41d2-83fd-945c5732f686',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Hono's OpenAPIHono — Auto-Docs, Validation, and Types from One Zod Schema$escape$,
  $escape$Hono ships `@hono/zod-openapi` — a first-party package that turns Zod schemas directly into an OpenAPI 3.0 spec and a live Swagger UI, FastAPI-style but with full TypeScript inference baked in.

The key primitive is `createRoute()`. You declare method, path, request shape (params, query, body), and response schemas in one object. Hono validates incoming requests against those schemas automatically — `c.req.valid('param')` returns the typed, already-validated value. No separate validation middleware needed.

Swap `new Hono()` for `new OpenAPIHono()`, define routes with `app.openapi()`, then mount the spec with `app.doc()` and the Swagger UI via `@hono/swagger-ui`. The spec is generated live from the same Zod schemas enforcing runtime types.

This eliminates the usual triangle problem: docs drift from code, code drifts from validation, validation drifts from types. With `OpenAPIHono`, one Zod schema is authoritative for all three. Unlike NestJS decorators or Django REST Framework's `@api_view`, there's no reflection magic — just plain objects, Zod, and zero ceremony.$escape$,
  $escape$import { OpenAPIHono, createRoute, z } from '@hono/zod-openapi'
import { swaggerUI } from '@hono/swagger-ui'

const app = new OpenAPIHono()
const UserSchema = z.object({ id: z.string(), name: z.string() })

const route = createRoute({
  method: 'get', path: '/users/{id}',
  request: { params: z.object({ id: z.string() }) },
  responses: { 200: { content: { 'application/json': { schema: UserSchema } }, description: 'User' } },
})

app.openapi(route, (c) => {
  const { id } = c.req.valid('param')
  return c.json({ id, name: 'Alice' })
})

app.get('/ui', swaggerUI({ url: '/doc' }))
app.doc('/doc', { openapi: '3.0.0', info: { title: 'My API', version: 'v1' } })$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
